nt|^b@2^z@3Let's have a look at how the recommended spade opening lead might lead to the defeat of South's 3NT contract. First an important question: Which spade to lead? |
pg| ***** 32 ***** |


at|From a trick-taking point of view it does not matter which spade you lead. All 6 of West's spades are touching each other. In poker West's spades would be called a 6-card straight flush. In bridge they are called equals. |
