|cp||at|We have spent a lot of time discussing how to decide which suit to select as your opening lead against a notrump contract. Once you have decided which suit to lead, you have to decide which card to lead from that suit.

It has been mentioned several times that there exists a table of standard opening leads that can be used to help guide you as to which card to lead from a given suit against notrump. Unlike deciding which suit to lead, deciding which card to lead is very rarely a matter of judgment - you should almost always adhere to the guidelines presented here for deciding which card to lead from a given suit.

The reason why it is correct to always lead the same card from a given holding in a suit is because this practice will make it easier for your partner to defend accurately. Remember, your partner cannot see your hand when he is defending, but you can help him to visualize which cards you were dealt with the card that you select for your opening lead.

|
