hf|m|lb|*CWhich card would you lead?^^d7^d97642|

hc|d7|ht|m|cs|3|at|^-{ |ih|pd97642|at|}
^-
The standard opening lead from a suit with 4 or more cards and no honor cards is the 2nd highest card, the @D7 in this example.

Some bridge players prefer to lead 4th best (the @D4 in this case) from long weak suits, but the modern tendency is to lead 2nd highest from these holdings. The theory is that leading 2nd highest will often make it easier for your partner to know that you are weak in the suit that you led. On some deals this knowledge will make it easier for partner to defend effectively.

