The @H3 is the standard opening lead from this holding. Lead the smallest card from a 3-card holding that is headed by an honor card. Remember that the @H10 is considered to be an honor card! If the holding above contained the @H9 instead of the @H6 or @H3 then it would be correct to lead the @H10. The reason is that @H1093 is a 3-card holding headed by a 2-card sequence and the highest card should be led from such holdings.

